events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New York Knicks
Golden State Warriors at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier hit an off-balance jumper from the left corner as time expired to give the Charlotte Hornets a wild 102-100 victory over the Golden State Warriors on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, Hornets capitalize on Green's blow up, beat Warriors

events.name: Miami Heat at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Kendrick Nunn scored 27 points, Jimmy Butler had 24 points and eight rebounds, and the Miami Heat held off the Los Angeles Lakers 96-94 Saturday night in an NBA Finals rematch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat hold off depleted Lakers 96-94 in NBA Finals rematch

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 38 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the slumping Sacramento Kings 122-114 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 38, Bulls hold off struggling Kings 122-114

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 23 points, hitting five of the Phoenix Suns' franchise-record 24 3-in a 128-97 romp over the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns hit team-record 24 3s, blow out short-handed Grizzlies

events.name: Washington Wizards at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had 27 points, 13 assists and 11 rebounds, and the Washington Wizards snapped Portland's six-game win streak with a 118-111 victory over Damian Lillard and the Trail Blazers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook gets triple-double as Wizards beat Trail Blazers
